Ensure the XDMCP packet buffer is allocated before sending responses.

GDM reuses one XdmcpBuffer for XDMCP receive and response paths.  The
response helpers assume the buffer already has writable storage and ignore
XdmcpWriteHeader() failures before writing additional fields.  Allocate the
buffer when the display factory is initialized so XDMCP replies cannot
dereference a null data pointer.

Not suitable for upstream; legacy XDMCP support has been removed upstream.

--- a/daemon/gdm-xdmcp-display-factory.c
+++ b/daemon/gdm-xdmcp-display-factory.c
@@ -3413,6 +3413,11 @@
 
         factory->session_serial = g_random_int ();
 
+        factory->buf.data = g_malloc0 (XDM_MAX_MSGLEN);
+        factory->buf.size = XDM_MAX_MSGLEN;
+        factory->buf.pointer = 0;
+        factory->buf.count = 0;
+
         /* Fetch and store local hostname in XDMCP friendly format */
         hostbuf[1023] = '\0';
         if G_UNLIKELY (gethostname (hostbuf, 1023) != 0) {
@@ -3461,6 +3466,7 @@
         g_free (factory->hostname);
         g_free (factory->multicast_address);
         g_free (factory->willing_script);
+        g_free (factory->buf.data);
 
         /* FIXME: Free servhost */
 
